  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the chicken thighs, potatoes, cinnamon stick, and red pepper flakes. Cook for 5 minutes, until the chicken starts to brown.",
    "Add the tomato paste and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the chicken broth and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Stir in the fresh parsley.",
    "Serve hot with a squeeze of lemon juice and a side of pita bread, if desired."
